caption: Table 1: Comparison of performance under six possible testing conditions of inter-modality missingness and the complete-modality testing condition on the MOSI and MOSEI datasets. T-test is conducted on “Avg.” column. * indicates that p < 0.05 (compared with the SOTA CorrKD).
description: This table compares the performance of various models on the MOSI and MOSEI datasets under different conditions of missing modalities.  It shows the average F1 scores for each model under six scenarios of missing data (only one modality available, two modalities available etc.), and also includes results when all modalities are available.  The results are statistically analyzed using a t-test to compare against the state-of-the-art (SOTA) CorrKD model, highlighting significant improvements of the proposed HRLF model.

caption: Table 2: Comparison of performance under six possible testing conditions of inter-modality missingness and the complete-modality testing condition on the IEMOCAP dataset. T-test is conducted on "Avg." column. * indicates that p < 0.05 (compared with the SOTA CorrKD).
description: This table compares the performance of various models on the IEMOCAP dataset under different conditions of missing modalities.  It shows the average F1 scores for each model across six scenarios with varying degrees of missing modalities (only language, audio, visual, language & audio, language & visual, audio & visual modalities available) and a complete modality scenario.  A significant test (t-test) was used to compare the performance of the proposed HRLF model against the state-of-the-art CorrKD model, highlighting where HRLF shows statistically significant improvement.
